  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "Unlike lateral position, depth $z_c$ is encoded purely through the expansion of the PSF variance $\\sigma(z_c)^2$. Applying the chain rule to the forward model, the sensitivity of the signal to depth changes is:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n$$ \\mathbb{E} (\\hat{\\theta} - \\theta) = 0 $$\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhere the derivative of the blur variance with respect to depth is:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n$$g: \\theta \\to \\chi, \\quad \\theta \\mapsto \\mathbb{E} \\left[f\\right]$$\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSubstituting the Gaussian PSF derivative, we find:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n$$ \\mathbb{E} (\\hat{\\theta} - \\theta) = 0 $$\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIntegrating this squared gradient over the sensor plane yields the continuous Fisher Information $I_{zz}$. Just as with the lateral coordinates, we evaluate this integral at the two physical limits.\r\nYou can see the analytical results in the cell below. The first 2 equations represent the fisher information for signal and background regimes specifically, and the final 2 are the lower bounds for the same.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {},
   "executionSummary": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* ========================================== *)\r\n(* 7. Evaluating FIM Limits for Depth (InfoZZ)*)\r\n(* ========================================== *)\r\n\r\n(* The squared gradient for Z *)\r\ngradZSquared = FullSimplify[gradG[zc]^2];\r\n\r\n(* Limit 1: Photon-Noise Limited (\\[Beta] - 0) *)\r\nintegrandZPhoton = FullSimplify[gradZSquared / (Nphotons * psf[x, y, xc, yc, zc])];\r\n\r\nInfoZZPhoton = Integrate[\r\n  integrandZPhoton, \r\n  {x, -Infinity, Infinity}, {y, -Infinity, Infinity},\r\n  Assumptions - {\\[Sigma]0  0, zR  0, Nphotons  0, zc \\[Element] Reals}\r\n]\r\n\r\n(* Limit 2: Background-Noise Limited (\\[Beta] dominates) *)\r\nintegrandZBackground = FullSimplify[gradZSquared / \\[Beta]];\r\n\r\nInfoZZBackground = Integrate[\r\n  integrandZBackground, \r\n  {x, -Infinity, Infinity}, {y, -Infinity, Infinity},\r\n  Assumptions - {\\[Sigma]0  0, zR  0, Nphotons  0, \\[Beta]  0, zc \\[Element] Reals}\r\n]\r\n\r\n(* ========================================== *)\r\n(* 8. The Depth CRLBs                         *)\r\n(* ========================================== *)\r\n\r\ncrlbZPhoton = FullSimplify[1 / InfoZZPhoton]\r\ncrlbZBackground = FullSimplify[1 / InfoZZBackground]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wexpr\"><wgraph class=\"resizable\" style=\"width:56.4px;height:25.2px;\" aspect-ratio=\"0.446809\" tabIndex=\"-1\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></wgraph></div>",
