  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "To formally prove the temporal scaling limits of the Event Sensor, we must map our macroscopic FIM back to the spatial parameter space using the chain rule (the Jacobian).Let $\\theta_i$ be an arbitrary spatial parameter (e.g., $x_c$ or $z_c$). The Spatial Fisher Information $I_{\\theta_i}$ is the quadratic form of the macroscopic FIM projected through the Jacobian vector $J$:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n$$ \\mathbb{E} (\\hat{\\theta} - \\theta) = 0 $$\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWe evaluate this with respect to the integration time $T$. We define the base photon arrival rate as $\\bar{\\mu}$ and the differential photon rate as $\\bar{\\nu}$. Consequently, the macroscopic parameters and their spatial derivatives scale linearly with time:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n$$g: \\theta \\to \\chi, \\quad \\theta \\mapsto \\mathbb{E} \\left[f\\right]$$\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n$$ \\mathbb{E} (\\hat{\\theta} - \\theta) = 0 $$\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBy substituting these temporal relationships into $I_{\\theta_i}$, we yield a continuous analytical expression for the spatial Fisher Information purely as a function of the integration interval $T$. We then evaluate the limits of this expression at the extrema ($T \\to 0$ and $T \\to \\infty$) to definitively establish the bounding behavior of the sensor.\r\n",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "mime": "text/markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {},
   "executionSummary": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* ========================================== *)\r\n(* 12. Spatial FIM and Asymptotic Scaling     *)\r\n(* ========================================== *)\r\n\r\n\\[Mu]Sub = \\[Mu]Rate * T;\r\n\\[Nu]Sub = \\[Nu]Rate * T;\r\n\r\nd\\[Mu] = d\\[Mu]Rate * T;\r\nd\\[Nu] = d\\[Nu]Rate * T;\r\njacobian = {d\\[Mu], d\\[Nu]};\r\n\r\ntemporalFIM = FullSimplify[eventMacroscopicFIM /. {\\[Mu] -> \\[Mu]Sub, \\[Nu] -> \\[Nu]Sub, \\[Sigma]q -> \\[Sigma]q}];\r\n\r\nspatialInfo = FullSimplify[jacobian . temporalFIM . jacobian];\r\n\r\n(* ========================================== *)\r\n(* 13. Evaluating the Extreme Limits          *)\r\n(* ========================================== *)\r\n\r\n(* --- Extreme 1: The Short Integration Limit (T -> 0) --- *)\r\nshortIntegrationProof = FullSimplify[\r\n  Limit[spatialInfo, T -> 0, Assumptions -> {\\[Mu]Rate > 0, \\[Nu]Rate > 0, \\[Sigma]q > 0}]\r\n]\r\n\r\n(* --- Extreme 2: The Long Integration Limit (T -> Infinity) --- *)\r\nlongIntegrationProof = FullSimplify[\r\n  Limit[spatialInfo, T -> Infinity, Assumptions -> {\\[Mu]Rate > 0, \\[Nu]Rate > 0, \\[Sigma]q > 0}]\r\n]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
